# Allow only what the per-crate Dockerfiles need at build context.
# The build context is repo-root for every image (each Dockerfile
# COPYs the workspace members it needs); each crate's own Dockerfile
# and smoke.sh live alongside the crate it builds.
#
# `.ci-prebuilt/` is the staging directory the CI runner populates
# with the binary it built on the host (`BINARY_SOURCE=prebuilt`
# branch of every Dockerfile). It's empty in local-dev — local builds
# default to `BINARY_SOURCE=source` and ignore the directory.
*
!.ci-prebuilt/
!.ci-prebuilt/**
!admin-api/
!admin-api/**
!admin-core/
!admin-core/**
!admin-ui/
!admin-ui/**
# The trunk-emitted bundle is *generated* by `trunk build --release`
# inside the container builder stage (or by CI's host-side trunk run),
# so any host-side `dist/` is stale at best and lockfile-poisoning at
# worst. Strip it from the build context, but keep the `.gitkeep`
# placeholder so the empty directory is created (include_dir! refuses
# a missing path; trunk itself prefers to populate an existing dir).
admin-ui/wasm/dist/*
!admin-ui/wasm/dist/.gitkeep
# bootstrap/ is no longer in any image (RFE #106 PR4 round 3 retired
# its Dockerfile + Earthfile target). But it's still a workspace
# member (test-only seed helper used by 3 integration tests), so the
# sibling Dockerfiles' `cargo metadata` / `cargo build --workspace`
# steps still need its manifest on disk in the build context.
!bootstrap/
!bootstrap/**
!session-broker/
!session-broker/**
!config-broker/
!config-broker/**
!control-plane/
!control-plane/**
!db/
!db/**
!launcher/
!launcher/**
!tools/
!tools/**
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
